race.description: Poppa Joe Memorial Showcase Mdn Plate
race.comment: ZIGGY ROSE (10) was hard to miss when resuming from a brief spell last start over 1300m at Goulburn, winding up late only to just miss out in an impressive performance. Nicely placed out to this trip on a quick back-up. Would prefer a bit more pace in the race but she shouldn't be too far back from the decent draw and looks the testing material. HELIGAN (11) stepped out beyond 1400m for the first time last start and did a fair job in finishing sixth at Wagga Riverside. Should improve off that run and in a plain affair he gets his chance. PITCH 'N' TOSS (8) was beaten a whisker over the mile at Kembla two back then failed to measure up in town last time. Nicely placed in this company and she looks one of the better hopes. LANDMARK LADY (6) is struggling to make her mark. Best recent effort was a fourth here at this trip three back. In the mix on that performance. ELITE DELIGHT (5) is new to this trip but is by Adelaide so she should run it out.
